'''Gode Venkata Juggarow''' (1817–1856) was an Indian [[astronomer]] and instrument maker. He was one of the few Indians who started and operated an astronomical [[observatory]] in British India at [[Visakhapatnam]]. He started his own observatory in Visakhapatnam at his residence in Daba Gardens.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Rao|first=N Kameshwar|author2=A Vagiswari |author3=Christina Birdie |title=Early pioneers of telescopic astronomy in India: G. V. Juggarow and  his observatory|journal=Current Science|date=25 May 2011|volume=100|issue=10|pages=1575|url=http://www.ias.ac.in/currsci/25may2011/1575.pdf|accessdate=1 June 2011}}</ref>

