'''Mouyassue virus''' is a novel, single-stranded, enveloped, negative-sense RNA [[orthohantavirus]].<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Weiss | first1 = S | last2 = Witkowski | first2 = PT | last3 = Auste | first3 = B | last4 = Nowak | first4 = K | last5 = Weber | first5 = N | last6 = Fahr | first6 = J | display-authors = 6 | last7 = et al | year = 2012 | title = Hantavirus in bat, Sierra Leone | journal = Emerg Infect Dis | volume = 18 | issue = | pages = 159–61 | doi=10.3201/eid1801.111026 | pmid=22261176 | pmc=3310113}}</ref>

== Natural reservoir ==

The [[banana pipistrelle]] (''Neoromicia nanus'') found in the Côte d'Ivoire is the natural reservoir of Mouyassue virus.<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Sumibcay L, Kadjo B, Gu SH, Kang HJ, Lim BK, Cook JA, Song JW, Yanagihara R |title=Divergent lineage of a novel hantavirus in the banana pipistrelle (''Neoromicia nanus'') in Côte d'Ivoire |journal=Virol. J. |volume=9 |issue= |pages=34 |year=2012 |pmid=22281072 |pmc=3331809 |doi=10.1186/1743-422X-9-34 |url=https://virologyj.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/1743-422X-9-34}}</ref> It shares a common lineage with the [[Magboi virus]] (MGBV) found in the hairy split-faced bat (''[[Nycteris hispida]]'') in Sierra Leone <ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Weiss | first1 = S | last2 = Witkowski | first2 = PT | last3 = Auste | first3 = B | last4 = Nowak | first4 = K | last5 = Weber | first5 = N | last6 = Fahr | first6 = J | display-authors = 6 | last7 = et al | year = 2012 | title = Hantavirus in bat, Sierra Leone | journal = Emerg Infect Dis | volume = 18 | issue = | pages = 159–61 | doi = 10.3201/eid1801.111026 | pmid=22261176 | pmc=3310113}}</ref>

